cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper focuses on natural language processing and machine learning techniques to classify argument components in classroom discussions. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval and classification, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.CY (Computers and Society).
